cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SD 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about improving neural machine translation models. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes new data augmentation methods to improve the robustness of NMT models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of NMT models, which is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions utilizing noise from external data in the form of speech transcripts, which could be related to speech recognition and computer vision. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with speech transcripts and noise in the input, which could be related to sound processing.
